{"actual_usd":0.123685,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":151,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24284,"reply":"\"No... I wouldn't put it that way.\" *I rub a thumb against a dry streak of clay on my apron, thinking how easy it is to split one living thing into parts.* \"The cross is where Christ actually bore sin and gave himself up; the resurrection is the Father's vindication of that work, and the victory of it made public. You can distinguish them, sure—but if you make the cross 'just suffering,' you've thinned the heart out of it.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"I'd say this instead: the cross and resurrection belong together like seed and sprout—one saving work, not rivals. What have you been reading that's pressing the question that way?\"","rolling_24h_usd":57.482170000000025,"run_id":"a3cc9c19-f6d7-4735-9141-90d404d6a805"}
